<Link id="l00028" /><CodeLine lineNumber="28"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// particular size (called the Block Size), and whose chunks may not be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00029" /><CodeLine lineNumber="29"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// necessarily contiguous.  The arrangement of these chunks MSF the file</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="30"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// is described by some other metadata contained within the MSF file.  In</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00031" /><CodeLine lineNumber="31"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the case of a standard MSF Stream, the layout of the stream&#39;s blocks</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// itself, the layout is described by an array at a fixed location within</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the MSF.  MappedBlockStream provides methods for reading from and writing</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00094" /><CodeLine lineNumber="94"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We just store the allocator by reference.  We use this to allocate</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00095" /><CodeLine lineNumber="95"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// contiguous memory for things like arrays or strings that cross a block</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00096" /><CodeLine lineNumber="96"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// boundary, and this memory is expected to outlive the stream.  For example,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00097" /><CodeLine lineNumber="97"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// someone could create a stream, read some stuff, then close the stream, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00098" /><CodeLine lineNumber="98"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// we would like outstanding references to fields to remain valid since the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00099" /><CodeLine lineNumber="99"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// entire file is mapped anyway.  Because of that, the user must supply the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00100" /><CodeLine lineNumber="100"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// allocator to allocate broken records from.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00101" /><CodeLine lineNumber="101"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a8e612822d4ba7bb36c9c79582a567108">BumpPtrAllocator</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/regallocbasic-cpp/#ad5d00e1d77644d95847b9bf8da12b759">Allocator</a>;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00103" /><CodeLine lineNumber="103"><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;;</span></CodeLine>
